# Evaluation Criteria

1. **Does it do what it is supposed to do?** — Every feature in the Features Request is covered across the per-track specs. No feature is missing implementation details.
2. **Does it work well?** — All track specs are internally consistent. Any UI track's API references match the api_contract (when present); any api track implements every endpoint declared in the api_contract.
3. **Is it reasonably well designed?** — No duplication across documents. The api_contract (when present) is the single source of truth for cross-track interfaces.
4. **Is it safe?** — Authentication and authorization are properly specified. No endpoints are missing auth requirements. Input validation is addressed at the right boundary.
5. **No obvious scaling issues?** — Data models support expected load. No N+1 query patterns. Pagination is specified where needed.
{% if figma_sources is defined and figma_sources %}
6. **Does it reflect the designs?** — Design tokens (colors, typography, spacing) are incorporated into the relevant UI track. Component names from Figma are referenced. Page/screen layouts match the designs.{% if figma_mcp_available == "true" %} Use Figma MCP tools to verify.{% endif %}
{% endif %}

